1. Understanding Red Hat Identity Management
---------------------------------------------
  - Preparing Identify Management Installation
    ------------------------------------------
      - Set up host name resolving
      - Disabled nscd 
      - Disable LDAP
      - Disable Kerberos Service
      - Open port in firewall
 Installing IPA-Server 'Redhat doesn't requires it.'
      - yum -y install ipa-server bind nds-ldap
        - ipa-server-install
      - systemctl restart sshd to obtain Kerberos Credentials
      - verify kerberos auth: 
        - default admin = kintadmin
      - verify IPA access
        - ipa user-find admin
  
  Kerberos Ticket?:
    - Before managing IdM server, it needs ticket for the admin user:
      - kinit admin   <--- generate ticket
      - klist         <--- show ticket validity
  
  Creating User Accounts
    - kinit admin
    - ipa user-add mathew
    - ipa passwd mathew
    - ipa user-find mathew


